Our recent trip to Bordeaux indicates "prices for the good Chateau bottled wines have marched up continuously since the beginning of this year because of the publicity showered upon the 1959 vintage, the increased world demand for Clarets, particularly from England, West Germany and the Benelux countries". The better Chateau bottled wines of 1952, 1953 and 1955 are practically unobtainable in Bordeaux or hopelessly expensive. In light of this, this offering provides an exceptional opportunity to acquire some of the better Chateau bottled Clarets at prices considerably below the current market.
